## Industry Best Practices to Follow

### 1. Code Quality & Standards

#### Java/Spring Boot Best Practices
- **Follow SOLID principles**
- **Use dependency injection** - Let Spring manage your beans
- **Separate concerns** - Controller → Service → Repository pattern
- **Use DTOs** - Don't expose entities directly in APIs
- **Implement proper exception handling** - Use @ControllerAdvice for global exception handling
- **Use Lombok** - Reduce boilerplate with @Data, @Builder, @Slf4j
- **Write meaningful logs** - Use SLF4J with structured logging
- **Configuration externalization** - Use application.yml and environment variables
- **API versioning** - Include /api/v1/ in all endpoints
- **Input validation** - Use @Valid and @Validated with Bean Validation
- **Use profiles** - dev, test, prod profiles for different environments

#### Example Controller Pattern:
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping(\"/api/v1/videos\")
@Slf4j
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class UploadController {
    
    private final UploadService uploadService;
    
    @PostMapping(\"/upload\")
    public ResponseEntity<UploadResponse> uploadVideo(
            @Valid @RequestParam(\"file\") MultipartFile file,
            @Valid @ModelAttribute VideoMetadataRequest metadata) {
        
        log.info(\"Received upload request for video: {}\", metadata.getTitle());
        
        try {
            UploadResponse response = uploadService.processUpload(file, metadata);
            return ResponseEntity.ok(response);
        } catch (InvalidFileException e) {
            log.error(\"Invalid file upload: {}\", e.getMessage());
            throw new ResponseStatusException(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST, e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}
```

#### Example Service Pattern:
```java
@Service
@Slf4j
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class UploadService {
    
    private final S3Service s3Service;
    private final KafkaProducerService kafkaProducerService;
    private final VideoValidator videoValidator;
    
    @Transactional
    public UploadResponse processUpload(MultipartFile file, VideoMetadataRequest metadata) {
        // Validate
        videoValidator.validate(file);
        
        // Generate unique ID
        String videoId = UUID.randomUUID().toString();
        
        // Upload to S3
        String s3Url = s3Service.uploadRawVideo(videoId, file);
        log.info(\"Video uploaded to S3: {}\", s3Url);
        
        // Produce Kafka event
        VideoUploadEvent event = VideoUploadEvent.builder()
                .videoId(videoId)
                .s3Url(s3Url)
                .originalFilename(file.getOriginalFilename())
                .fileSize(file.getSize())
                .build();
        
        kafkaProducerService.sendUploadEvent(event);
        log.info(\"Upload event produced for video: {}\", videoId);
        
        return UploadResponse.builder()
                .videoId(videoId)
                .status(\"UPLOADED\")
                .message(\"Video uploaded successfully\")
                .build();
    }
}
